 n^{2} = 4^{{\log_{2}}(n)}. 
a^{\log_a(x)} = x \,\,\,\,\,\, \forall a,x >0
4^{\log_2(n)} = (2^{2})^{\log_2(n)} = (2^{\log_2(n)})^2 = n^2
4^{\log_2n}=\left(2^2\right)^{\log_2n}=2^{2\log_2n}=\left(2^{\log_2n}\right)^2=n^2
\log_{2}
n^{2} = 4^{{\log_{2}} n}
2\log_{2}n =2\log_{2}n 
n=2^t
n^2=(2^t)^2=2^{2t}
4^{Log_2 n}=4^{Log_2 2^t}=4^t=(2^2)^t=2^{2t}
\square
